## When to use this pattern

Use this pattern at the end of a survey or transaction when the user has completed their task.

## How to use this pattern

A confirmation page help reassure users that they have completed a survey or transaction, and helps them to understand what to expect next.

When using this pattern you <strong>should</strong>:
{{
    onsList({
        "itemsList": [
            {
                "text": 'include relevant details in the success panel to reassure the user it was completed correctly. For example, the household address they completed the survey for, or the phone number they entered to get an access code.'
            },
            {
                "text": 'reassure the user by letting them know what will happen to their information or what to expect next, such as the sender ID of a text or email they will receive'
            },
            {
                "text": 'provide a way to resend anything that should have been sent as part of the transaction in case the user didn’t receive it'
            },
            {
                "text": 'include links to the next steps of the process or information the user is likely to need next'
            }
        ]
    })
}}

When using this pattern you <strong>should not include</strong>:
{{
    onsList({
        "itemsList": [
            {
                "text": 'a back link to the previous page'
            }
        ]
    })
}}

When using this pattern you should also consider including:
{{
