            }
        ]
    })
}}

## Confirmation email

Users often want to save a record of the confirmation that they have submitted a survey, especially if it is mandatory, like the census. They want proof to show, for example, a member of the field staff visiting to check their household has completed the census.

You should use the confirmation page to ask the user for their email address to send them a confirmation email. Use the [check answers pattern](/patterns/check-answers) to ask the user to confirm their email address is correct before sending the it.

The confirmation email should contain a unique reference to the users particular survey, to reassure them that it is sufficient evidence of them having completed and submitted the survey.

