## Research on this pattern

During the development of Census 2021, research revealed that asking the user for their email address (to send confirmation) before the survey confirmation page, prevented some users from submitting their answers.

The same research also showed that users:
{{
    onsList({
        "itemsList": [
            {
                "text": 'want to be sent proof that they have completed the census for their household, to avoid receiving a fine'
            },
            {
                 "text": 'expect a reference number in the confirmation email, unique to their particular submission'
            },
            {
                 "text": 'are not inclined to help promote a survey like the census on their social media, by sharing the fact they have completed it'
            }
        ]
    })
}}

Research has also shown that users want to save a copy of the confirmation page. A “print this page” link was not a suitable action for those wanting to save it for their records, as most were unfamiliar with printing to a pdf file.

Business survey respondents also expect to be able to save a record of their answers after submitting a survey. This is typically required to be able to compare data across time. More research is required on the pattern for saving survey answers.

